social_posts.post_text:
Usually y’all just see my hands on here, and I didn’t want any rumors started up I was thing on Addams family 🤲 so I thought I’d show y’all a few photos from a fun shoot I did with @avonnephotostudios @avonnephotography in my kitchen ❤️ This is my happy place for fun and creativity and I’ve loved making friends online who like to play with their food too! A couple of y’all have followed me through culinary school and I’ve been so humbled and appreciative of your encouragement 🙏

Going to be changing up kitchens here soon as we stay on the road for baseball season ⚾️ but still making hearty meals for my picky guy and a balance of slightly less hearty meals for myself.

I like ALL food so you will see everything from air fryer desserts, to healthy recipes from culinary school, to tried and true southern meals I learned from my Mom and Grandmother. I only post the recipes I think are definitely worth making again and again. Cooking for picky eaters is my favorite challenge, perhaps because I am married to the 👑 

Just wanted to say I’ve had the most fun sharing some of my favorite recipes, meeting and hearing your cooking stories, finding out I’m definitely not the only one with a cruller obsession, and learning some new tips from y’all, so thank you!! Alright, now back to the 🤲

🍉 If you need an easy by the pool Drink idea for this afternoon, might I recommend ✨ her ✨ 

WATERMELON MINT LIME SLUSHIES 
3 C frozen watermelon 
1 C frozen strawberries 
1 tbsp honey or syrup
5 mint leaves (plus mint for garnish)
1 lime juiced 

Blend, garnish and enjoy 🍉 head over for more summertime treats on my page ☀️

The Easiest Roast 101 recipe of all time. If you cant cook or need 1 easy impressive meal ANYONE can make- this is It. If you lived anywhere in eastern NC my Grandmother probably even made this roast for you. It’s 3 easy, no prep ingredients and is incredibly delicious comfort food.

Recipe:
1 3-4 lb Beef Chuck Roast
3 Cups of water
3/4 Cup Dales steak seasoning marinade (at most groceries, wal-mart and Amazon)

Cook in crockpot for 8-10 hours on low or in oven at 200 for at least 8 hours. 

I put mine in the crockpot or oven right when I wake up. Because it is in so much liquid it just gets more and more tender and doesn’t dry out giving you alot of room for error. 
Theres not much to making it but if there’s one recipe I could have everyday for the rest of my life it would definitely be Grandmothers Roast ❤️ (If you’re in California it’s a good rainy day recipe 🫶)

🥕 Crispy garlic parmesan carrots I could eat like French fries 💕 

* 1 pound whole carrots
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/2 teaspoon salt
* 1/4 teaspoon pepper
* 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
* 1/2 teaspoon paprika
* 1/2 teaspoon onion powder 
* 3 tbsp minced garlic 
* 1 and ¼ cups fresh parmesan cheese (freshly grated or shredded)
* Parsley to top 

* Peel carrots and cut them into thirds. cut each piece down the middle so you have a flat side on each piece
* In a medium bowl, add olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika, minced garlic, and 1/4 cup of the parmesan cheese. Mix with a fork until everything is combined.
* Add the carrots to the bowl and toss to coat all of the carrots. 
* Add the remaining cup of parmesan cheese to a plate and press the flat side of each carrot in the cheese. The cheese should stick to the carrot coating the bottom. 
* Add each coated carrot, cheese side down on a non-stick baking sheet or casserole dish (parchment paper helps!)
* Bake in the oven at 375 F for 25-30 minutes or until the cheese on the bottom looks browned and crispy.

End of summer watermelons are so juicy and sweet! 🍉 Extending summertime with this WATERMELON CARPACCIO 😍

-shaved or cubed watermelon 🍉 
-Chopped Walnuts 
-Drizzled Honey 🍯 
-Drizzled good Olive oil 
-Sprinkle of fresh Mint leaves or basil 🌿 
-Sprinkle of Feta 

There are not exact measurements to this one it’s a little sprinkle of everything to create your perfect bite 🫶

Cornbread Cookies with honey buttercream are actually really easy to make and one of the best Crumbl cookies ever. Here is a small batch recipe so you can try some this fall 🍁 They are incredibly delicious with or without frosting and wil approved 

cookies-
* 1/2 cup butter
* 1/2 cup light brown sugar
* 1/4 cup white sugar
* 2 tbsp cup honey
* 1 egg 
* 1 tsp vanilla
* 1 1/4 cup flour
* 1/2 cup cornmeal
* 1/2 tbsp cornstarch
* 1/2 tsp salt
* 1/2 tsp baking powder

Honey buttercream-
* 1/4 cup butter
* 1 tbsp honey
* 1 cup powdered sugar
* 1/2 tsp vanilla

Combine butter, brown sugar, and white sugar and mix for 5 min.  Add eggs, honey, and vanilla. Mix for 2 more minutes 
Add flour, cornmeal, cornstarch, salt, and baking powder. Mix until just combined.
For large crumbl cookies scoop 1/2 cup of dough and roll into a ball. Bake 13 min at 350. they won’t look quite done but they are in an excellent shape- Let the cookies cool

honey buttercream-
Combine butter and honey in a bowl. Mix for 3 minutes until well combined. Add powdered sugar and vanilla, and mix again for 2 minutes.
Add a scoop of the honey buttercream on top of each cookie and drizzle w honey if you want but honestly they’re so good alone

No cook dinner! Chopped Italian subs (or salads) went viral for a reason. They have so much flavor! You get a small piece of everything in every bite and it’s just beautiful 

Chop It Up: 
1 Tomato
3 slices Pepperoni
3 slices Genoa salami 
3 slices Black Forest ham
2 Cups Lettuce
1/4 C Mayo
3 slices Provolone
1/2 Red onion 
Handful of Banana Peppers

Dressing:
1/8 C Red wine vinegar 
1/4 C olive oil 
1 tsp Dijon Mustard 
Salt and pepper to taste 
1 tsp Dried oregano

🍋 Lemon Ricotta Pasta is creamy and delicious and filling and that’s all I can say 

* 1/2 lb pasta 
* 1 cup ricotta
* 1/3 cup grated Parm 
* 1 lemon zested 
* 1/2 lemon squeezed 
* 1 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil
* 1 clove minced garlic 
* salt and pepper
* 1/4 C Pasta water 

-Boil pasta 
-In separate bowl, combine ricotta, olive oil, parmesan cheese, garlic, lemon zest and juice, salt and pepper and pasta water once pasta is complete. 
-Drain, Pour pasta into bowl with lemon ricotta mixture and enjoy! 🍝

🍸 Happy weekend! Here’s a simple FROZEN SPICY MARGARITA recipe to elevate it even more! 🫶

Spicy Margs:
* 3 tbsp tequila
* 1 Tbsp triple sec 
* 2 Tbsp lime juice 
* 1 Tbsp. sugar (or honey)
* 1 cup ice
* 1/2 jalapeño (take out the seeds!)

Combine all and blend! 🌶️

🌽 My favorite cheesy corn dip with directions for the smoker or oven! All it takes is some chopping and throwing it in a baking dish. 🙌

3 cups corn 🌽 
1/2 C green chilies 
1/2 bar cream cheese
1 C chopped Gouda 🧀 
1/2 C Colby Jack
Juice of 1/2 Lime
1/2 cup sour cream
1 tbsp onion powder 🧅 
1 tbsp garlic powder 🧄 
1 tsp cumin 
I like to sprinkle the top with Tajin 🌶️ 

Add in baking dish, cover with foil, and Bake at 350 for 30 minutes in oven, or put in smoker for 1 hour at 300. Mix well and serve with some tasty chips

🥗 Warm Roasted Potato Sheet Pan salad gets me a little more hype to eat salad. It has capers, parmesan, and a super tasty red wine vinaigrette. This salad is perfect to me and super easy to put together if you want to try!

Dressing: 1/2 cup olive oil 1/4 cup red wine vinegar 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard  1 teaspoon dried oregano  salt and pepper
1/2 shallot 

1 ½ lbs red potatoes, cut in chunks
2 tablespoons olive oil
3 tbsp minced garlic 
4 teaspoons onion powder 
2 teaspoons salt 
1 bunch fresh asparagus
1 lb green beans 
1/2 C Parmesan Cheese
2 tbsp capers 
Bag Arugula 

Lay out veggies on sheet pan with parchment paper. Sprinkle with olive oil and cover with seasonings. Cook at 425 for 20 minutes. Let sit for 10 min then put over arugula. Top with capers and parmesan and dressing. I also add lemon because I want lemon on everything at all times

CHILI POT PIES make it feel like fall is here 😍🍂
Homemade chili with an easy jiffy cornbread crust are so tasty!

Chili:
*1 lb ground beef
* 2 1/2 tbsp chili powder
* 1 tbsp minced onion 
* 2 tbsp ground cumin
* 1 tbsp granulated sugar
* 1 tbsp garlic powder
* 1 1/2 tsp salt
* 1/2 tsp ground black pepper
* 1/4 tsp ground cayenne pepper if you want spice 🌶️ 
* 2 C beef broth
* 1 C diced tomatoes
* 2 cans pinto beans or red kidney beans, drained and rinsed
* 2 cans tomato paste

Cook ground beef, drain, add broth, seasonings, and remaining ingredients. Bring to boil then simmer for 25 minutes. 

Cornbread crust:
*Box of Jiffy
*1 egg
*1/3 C milk

Add chili to small bowls. Top with 1/2 C of cornbread mix and bake at 400 for 15 minutes!
